---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  pageHeading="Contact & Coordination"
  description="Get in touch about hosting Router 2, coordinating with KC mesh efforts, or just asking questions."
>
  <!-- Intro -->
  <section class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
    <h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold leading-tight text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">
      Let's talk about building the KC mesh
    </h2>
    <p class="text-xl text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
      This is a one-person project right now, but I'm actively looking for collaborators, Router 2 hosts, and anyone who wants to help build mesh infrastructure in Kansas City.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Primary Reasons to Contact -->
  <section class="mt-12 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
    <article class="rounded-3xl border-2 border-kc-red/30 bg-gradient-to-br from-kc-red/5 to-sunset-amber/5 p-6 dark:border-sunset-amber/20 dark:from-kc-red/10">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-kc-red dark:text-sunset-amber">I have a west-side site for Router 2</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
        This is the top priority. If you have elevation west of State Line Road (Johnson County, western KC) and you're willing to host Router 2, let's talk immediately.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="rounded-3xl border-2 border-kc-blue/30 bg-gradient-to-br from-kc-blue/5 to-kc-sky/10 p-6 dark:border-kc-sky/20 dark:from-kc-blue/10">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">I operate kansascitymesh.net</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
        I know you exist. I don't want to compete—I want to collaborate. Let's coordinate our efforts and build this together.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">I want to help build infrastructure</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
        Repeater site owner? Technical skills? Time to volunteer? All of these help. Reach out and tell me what you can contribute.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">I have questions about getting started</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
        Check the guides first, but if you're still stuck or confused, I'll help. New users welcome.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <!-- Contact Methods -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">How to reach me</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Email (Primary)</h3>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>Address:</strong> <a href="mailto:contact@kansascitymesh.live" class="text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">contact@kansascitymesh.live</a></p>
          <p><strong>Response time:</strong> Usually within 24-48 hours</p>
          <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Router 2 hosting inquiries, coordination with kansascitymesh.net, infrastructure discussions</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Meshtastic Direct Message</h3>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>Node name:</strong> KC-Router1 (visible if you're in coverage area)</p>
          <p><strong>Response time:</strong> I check the mesh app a few times daily</p>
          <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Testing your setup, mesh-specific questions, quick coordination if you're already on the network</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">GitHub Issues</h3>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>Repository:</strong> <a href="https://github.com/jeremyfuksa/kansascitymesh.live" class="text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">github.com/jeremyfuksa/kansascitymesh.live</a></p>
          <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Website bugs, content corrections, technical suggestions</p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Coordination Transparency -->
  <section class="mt-12 rounded-3xl border-2 border-kc-blue/30 bg-gradient-to-br from-kc-blue/5 to-kc-sky/10 p-6 sm:p-8 dark:border-kc-sky/20 dark:from-kc-blue/10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Coordination with kansascitymesh.net</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>
        <strong>I know there's an existing kansascitymesh.net operator.</strong> I found the domain registration while researching KC mesh activity.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>I don't want to compete. I want to collaborate.</strong> Two people trying to build the same infrastructure separately is stupid. We should coordinate.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Current status:</strong> Waiting to hear from kansascitymesh.net operator. If that's you, please reach out. Let's talk about combining efforts, coordinating router placements, and building this together.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-6">
      <a
        href="mailto:contact@kansascitymesh.live?subject=kansascitymesh.net%20coordination"
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-kc-blue px-6 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-cream-50 transition hover:bg-kc-red dark:bg-kc-sky dark:text-ink-900 dark:hover:bg-sunset-amber"
      >
        Contact about coordination →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What to Expect -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">What to expect when you contact me</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>
        <strong>I'm responsive but not instant.</strong> This is a side project. I'll reply within a day or two for most things, faster for urgent Router 2 hosting inquiries.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>I'm helpful but blunt.</strong> I'll answer your questions honestly. If I think you're overthinking something, I'll tell you. If the guides already answer your question, I'll point you there.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>I'm building this in public.</strong> Conversations about network architecture, router placements, and coordination are fair game for documenting publicly (anonymized if requested).
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Other Ways to Participate -->
  <section class="mt-12 rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 sm:p-8 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Don't need to contact me? Deploy without asking.</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>
        <strong>You don't need permission to join the mesh.</strong> Buy a device, configure it for KC mesh settings (915 MHz, LongFast), deploy it. That's it.
      </p>
      <p>
        The mesh is more valuable when more people are using it. Every node you deploy makes the network better.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
      <a href="/get-started/join" class="text-base font-medium text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">
        Setup guide for new nodes →
      </a>
      <a href="/get-started/hardware" class="text-base font-medium text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">
        Hardware recommendations →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA -->
  <section class="mt-12 text-center">
    <div class="inline-block rounded-3xl bg-gradient-to-br from-kc-blue to-kc-red p-8 text-cream-50 shadow-card md:p-10">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Questions? Router 2 site? Let's talk.</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-xl text-base opacity-95">
        Especially if you operate kansascitymesh.net or have a west-side site for Router 2. Those are priority conversations.
      </p>
      <a
        href="mailto:contact@kansascitymesh.live"
        class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-cream-50 px-8 py-3 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-kc-blue transition hover:bg-surface-200"
      >
        Send Email →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
